glish_Electric_Lightning"}
{"title_page": "Forever (Charli XCX song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 single by Charli XCX}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name        = Forever\n| type        = single\n| cover       = Charli XCX - Forever.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Regards Coupables\n| artist      = [[Charli XCX]]\n| album       = [[How I'm Feeling Now]]\n| released    = {{start date|2020|04|09|df=yes}}\n| recorded    = 6\u20138 April 2020<ref name= \"Pitchfork\">{{cite web |title=Listen to Charli XCX's New Song \"forever\"|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-charli-xcx-new-song-forever/?verso=true|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate= 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n| format      =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre       =\n*[[Pop music|Pop]]<ref name=\"spin\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2020/04/charli-xcx-shares-forever-from-upcoming-quarantine-album/|title=Charli XCX Shares 'Forever' From Upcoming Quarantine Album|date=9 April 2020|website=Spin}}</ref>\n*[[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"nme\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/charli-xcx-new-single-forever-2644319|title=Listen to Charli XCX's new self-isolation single 'Forever'|date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n| length      = {{duration|m=4|s=3}}\n| label       = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer      = \n* [[Charli XCX|Charlotte Aitchison]]\n* [[A. G. Cook|Alexander Guy Cook]]\n* [[BJ Burton]]\n| producer    = \n* [[A. G. Cook]] \n* [[BJ Burton]]\n| prev_title = [[Ringtone (Remix)]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|1O9xP4g8zfU|\"Forever\"}}|header=Audio video|type=single}}\n{{Extra album cover\n| header = Apple Music cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Charli XCX Forever Cover Art - Caroline Polachek.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Caroline Polachek\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n| header = Spotify cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Charli XCX- Forever Spotfiy cover.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Seth Bogart\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Forever'''\" (stylized in [[Letter case#All lowercase|all lowercase]]) is a song written and recorded by British singer [[Charli XCX]] from her upcoming fourth album ''[[How I'm Feeling Now]]'' (2020). Charli XCX produced the song with [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]], and it was released on 9 April 2020, by [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] as the lead single from the album. \"Forever\" is a [[Pop music|pop]] and [[synth-pop]] song that features [[dark wave]] and [[Electronic music|electronic]] influences.\n\n==Background and release==\nOn 7 April 2020, Charli XCX shared snippets of \"Forever\" on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-clip-album-2642649|title=Listen to a clip of Charli XCX\u2019s new song 'Forever' from upcoming quarantine album|date=7 April 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[NME]]|author=Tom Skinner}}</ref> On 8 April 2020, Charli XCX uploaded three photos of herself, shot by her boyfriend, to her [[Instagram]] and [[Twitter]] account and asked fans to vote for one photo to be the cover. On 9 April 2020, Charli XCX announced that \"Forever\" would be released at 07:30 PM [[British Summer Time|BST]] / 11:30 AM [[Pacific Standard Time|PST]] and premiere on [[BBC Radio 1]] as [[Annie Mac]]'s Hottest Record in the World.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248287541306036225 |title=\ud83d\udc93 FOREVER DROPS AT 7.30PM BST/11:30AM PST PREMIERING AS HOTTEST RECORD ON @ANNIEMAC ON @BBCR1!!!!! ARTWORK BY @SETHBOGARTOK!!! 2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS TO COME LATER IN THE DAY \ud83d\udc93 THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME CREATE THE FIRST SONG FROM \"HOW I\u2019M FEELING NOW\" \ud83d\udc93 |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> She also announced three official artworks for the single were commissioned.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248043315951370240 |title=fyi i am making multiple official artworks for every song I release before the album, maybe even multiple album covers too. the \"forever\" artwork will be based of the photo we selected together and will be visually interpreted by @SethBogartOK @carolineplz and @regardscoupable \ud83d\udc93 |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> One version was created by American artist [[Seth Bogart (artist)|Seth Bogart]] and used on [[Spotify]]; one version by French artist Regards Coupables, used on [[YouTube]] and [[Amazon Music]]<ref>{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Amazon Music |url=https://music.amazon.com/albums/B086WQ21WX |website=[[Amazon Music]]|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>; and one version by American singer-songwriter [[Caroline Polachek]], used on [[Apple Music]].\n\n==Composition==\n\"Forever\" was written by Charli XCX and produced by [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]]. It runs for four minutes and three seconds.<ref name= \"Spotify\">{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Spotify|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/0yl0sfY3TM3EDLPWghBkfc|website=[[Spotify]]|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Musically, it is a [[Pop music|pop]]<ref name=\"spin\"/> and [[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"nme\"/> song that features [[dark wave]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/music/charli-xcx/forever/|title=Charli XCX Returns to the Raves on \"Forever,\" The First Track From how i'm feeling now|date=9 April 2020|website=pastemagazine.com}}</ref> and [[Electronic music|electronic]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euphoriazine.com/blog/2020/04/new-music/tracks-charli-xcx-forever/|title=Charli XCX - Forever|date=9 April 2020}}</ref> influences. The song also features \"lo-fi beats and luminous synths\" with Charli singing about \"an everlasting love that will remain even if the relationship fades away or if they're not physically together\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2020/4/charli-xcx-forever-single-how-im-feeling-now-album-release-info|title=Charli XCX Drops Lovestruck \"Forever\" Single Recorded in Quarantine|last=Leung|first=Gabrielle|date=|website=Hyperbeast|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9355315/charli-xcx-forever-single|title=Charli XCX Loves You 'Forever' (Even While Social Distancing) in New Single|last=Cooper|first=Marcus|date=9 April 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nTrey Alston from ''[[MTV]]'' called the song a \"robotic ballad\" that was about \"sheer adoration, to the most mechanical degree\", in addition to writing that \"if toasters listened to songs when they made love, [this song] would be on their playlist. Alston described the opening of the song as a \"harsh opening of boiling synths [transitioning] into a slightly smoother sore throat of a cyborg who's doing its best impression of a lovestruck human\". Alston also felt that the sound was a \"Terminator-like landscape\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3162671/charli-xcx-forever-song-new-album-how-im-feeling-now/|title=Charli XCX's First Song She Made In Quarantine Is Here \u2014 And It's Wild|last=Alston|first=Trey|date=|website=MTV News|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> Justin Curto from [[Vulture magazine|''Vulture'']] called the song \"muted\" and \"somewhat dissonant\", that \"would sound right at home tacked on the end of [[Charli (album)|Charli]]''\".''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/charli-xcx-quarantine-song-forever.html|title=And on the Third Day, Charli XCX Dropped Her Quarantine Single|last=Curto|first=Justin|date=9 April 2020|website=Vulture|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Lake Schatz of [[Consequence of Sound|''Consequence of Sound'']] described the song as an \"emotional number\" that \"[wrestles] with intimacy issues \u2014 especially during this time of social distancing\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/04/stream-charli-xcx-forever-new-song/|title=Charli XCX delivers new song \"Forever\" from quarantine: Stream|last=Schatz|first=Lake|date=9 April 2020|website=Consequence of Sound|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''\u2019s Jem Aswad felt that the song \"bears many of the hallmarks of the prolific artist\u2019s work over the past couple of year\", including Charli\u2019s two mixtapes. Calling the melody \"indelible\", Aswad mentions Cook\u2019s trademark \"echoing synthesizers\" and how Charli uses auto tune as an \"instrument in itself rather than as pitch correction\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-quarantine-album-listen-1234576093/|title=Charli XCX Drops New Song, \u2018Forever,\u2019 From Forthcoming Quarantine Album (Listen)|last=Aswad|first=Jem|last2=|first2=|date=|website=Variety|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Michael Love Michael of [[Paper (magazine)|''Paper'']], felt that the message of the song was about \" reminiscing about the good times with an ex\", and while Charli was \"singing about the future, the production and overall feel of 'Forever' couldn't sound more relevant\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/bops-only-joey-labeija-2645691331.html?rebelltitem=1#rebelltitem1?rebelltitem=1|title=Bops Only: 10 Songs You Need to Start Your Weekend Right|last=Michael|first=Michael Love|date=10 April 2020|website=PAPER|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> James from ''[[Stereogum]]'' described the song as \"perfectly goofy and giddy\", \"something that sounds ephemeral but feels like it will last forever\". James also felt that there was nothing \"nothing slapdash\" about the track, writing that the lyrics talked about a \"part of the compressed reality we\u2019re all experiencing: being trapped in close to someone that you care about\" as the single \"switches between abrasive and elated\", \"[choosing] to embrace happiness in the moment\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2079877/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week-330/franchises/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week|title=The 5 Best Songs Of The Week|last=James|first=|date=|website=Stereogum|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136824746|title=Credits / forever / Charli XCX \u2013 TIDAL|website=[[Tidal (service)]]|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Charli XCX]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting, backing vocals\n* [[A. G. Cook]] \u2013 production, songwriting, drum programming, programming, synthesizer, vocal production, xylophone\n* [[BJ Burton]] \u2013 production, songwriting, drum programming, programming, synthesizer, vocal production\n* Geoff Swan \u2013 mixing\n* Stuart Hawkes \u2013 mastering\n* Niko Battistini \u2013 assistant mix engineer\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Region\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Format\n! scope=\"col\" | Label\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Various\n| 9 April 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| <ref name= \"Apple Music\">{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Apple Music|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/forever-single/1506988314|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate= 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Charli XCX}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Charli XCX songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Charli XCX]]\n\n{{2020s-single-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 single by Charli XCX}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name        = Forever\n| type        = single\n| cover       = Charli XCX - Forever.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Regards Coupables\n| artist      = [[Charli XCX]]\n| album       = [[How I'm Feeling Now]]\n| released    = {{start date|2020|04|09|df=yes}}\n| recorded    = 6\u20138 April 2020<ref name= \"Pitchfork\">{{cite web |title=Listen to Charli XCX's New Song \"forever\"|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-charli-xcx-new-song-forever/?verso=true|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate= 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n| format      =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre       =\n*[[Pop music|Pop]]<ref name=\"spin\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2020/04/charli-xcx-shares-forever-from-upcoming-quarantine-album/|title=Charli XCX Shares 'Forever' From Upcoming Quarantine Album|date=9 April 2020|website=Spin}}</ref>\n*[[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"nme\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/charli-xcx-new-single-forever-2644319|title=Listen to Charli XCX's new self-isolation single 'Forever'|date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n| length      = {{duration|m=4|s=3}}\n| label       = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer      = \n* [[Charli XCX|Charlotte Aitchison]]\n* [[A. G. Cook|Alexander Guy Cook]]\n* [[BJ Burton]]\n| producer    = \n* [[A. G. Cook]] \n* [[BJ Burton]]\n| prev_title = [[Ringtone (Remix)]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|1O9xP4g8zfU|\"Forever\"}}|header=Audio video|type=single}}\n{{Extra album cover\n| header = Apple Music cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Charli XCX Forever Cover Art - Caroline Polachek.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Caroline Polachek\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n| header = Spotify cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Charli XCX- Forever Spotfiy cover.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Designed by Seth Bogart\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Forever'''\" (stylized in [[Letter case#All lowercase|all lowercase]]) is a song written and recorded by British singer [[Charli XCX]] from her upcoming fourth album ''[[How I'm Feeling Now]]'' (2020). Charli XCX produced the song with [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]], and it was released on 9 April 2020, by [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] as the lead single from the album. \"Forever\" is a [[Pop music|pop]] and [[synth-pop]] song that features [[dark wave]] and [[Electronic music|electronic]] influences.\n\n==Background and release==\nOn 7 April 2020, Charli XCX shared snippets of \"Forever\" on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-clip-album-2642649|title=Listen to a clip of Charli XCX\u2019s new song 'Forever' from upcoming quarantine album|date=7 April 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[NME]]|author=Tom Skinner}}</ref> On 8 April 2020, Charli XCX uploaded three photos of herself, shot by her boyfriend, to her [[Instagram]] and [[Twitter]] account and asked fans to vote for one photo to be the cover. On 9 April 2020, Charli XCX announced that \"Forever\" would be released at 07:30 PM [[British Summer Time|BST]] / 11:30 AM [[Pacific Standard Time|PST]] and premiere on [[BBC Radio 1]] as [[Annie Mac]]'s Hottest Record in the World.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248287541306036225 |title=\ud83d\udc93 FOREVER DROPS AT 7.30PM BST/11:30AM PST PREMIERING AS HOTTEST RECORD ON @ANNIEMAC ON @BBCR1!!!!! ARTWORK BY @SETHBOGARTOK!!! 2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS TO COME LATER IN THE DAY \ud83d\udc93 THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME CREATE THE FIRST SONG FROM \"HOW I\u2019M FEELING NOW\" \ud83d\udc93 |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> She also announced three official artworks for the single were commissioned.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248043315951370240 |title=fyi i am making multiple official artworks for every song I release before the album, maybe even multiple album covers too. the \"forever\" artwork will be based of the photo we selected together and will be visually interpreted by @SethBogartOK @carolineplz and @regardscoupable \ud83d\udc93 |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> One version was created by American artist [[Seth Bogart (artist)|Seth Bogart]] and used on [[Spotify]]; one version by French artist Regards Coupables, used on [[YouTube]] and [[Amazon Music]]<ref>{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Amazon Music |url=https://music.amazon.com/albums/B086WQ21WX |website=[[Amazon Music]]|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>; and one version by American singer-songwriter [[Caroline Polachek]], used on [[Apple Music]].\n\n==Composition==\n\"Forever\" was written by Charli XCX and produced by [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]]. It runs for four minutes and three seconds.<ref name= \"Spotify\">{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Spotify|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/0yl0sfY3TM3EDLPWghBkfc|website=[[Spotify]]|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Musically, it is a [[Pop music|pop]]<ref name=\"spin\"/> and [[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"nme\"/> song that features [[dark wave]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/music/charli-xcx/forever/|title=Charli XCX Returns to the Raves on \"Forever,\" The First Track From how i'm feeling now|date=9 April 2020|website=pastemagazine.com}}</ref> and [[Electronic music|electronic]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euphoriazine.com/blog/2020/04/new-music/tracks-charli-xcx-forever/|title=Charli XCX - Forever|date=9 April 2020}}</ref> influences. The song also contains \"lo-fi beats and luminous synths\" that has Charli singing about \"an everlasting love that will remain even if the relationship fades away or if they're not physically together\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2020/4/charli-xcx-forever-single-how-im-feeling-now-album-release-info|title=Charli XCX Drops Lovestruck \"Forever\" Single Recorded in Quarantine|last=Leung|first=Gabrielle|date=|website=Hyperbeast|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9355315/charli-xcx-forever-single|title=Charli XCX Loves You 'Forever' (Even While Social Distancing) in New Single|last=Cooper|first=Marcus|date=9 April 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nTrey Alston from ''[[MTV]]'' called the song a \"robotic ballad\" that was about \"sheer adoration, to the most mechanical degree\", in addition to writing that \"if toasters listened to songs when they made love, [this song] would be on their playlist. Alston described the opening of the song as a \"harsh opening of boiling synths [transitioning] into a slightly smoother sore throat of a cyborg who's doing its best impression of a lovestruck human\". Alston also felt that the sound was a \"Terminator-like landscape\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3162671/charli-xcx-forever-song-new-album-how-im-feeling-now/|title=Charli XCX's First Song She Made In Quarantine Is Here \u2014 And It's Wild|last=Alston|first=Trey|date=|website=MTV News|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> Justin Curto from [[Vulture magazine|''Vulture'']] called the song \"muted\" and \"somewhat dissonant\", that \"would sound right at home tacked on the end of [[Charli (album)|Charli]]''\".''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/charli-xcx-quarantine-song-forever.html|title=And on the Third Day, Charli XCX Dropped Her Quarantine Single|last=Curto|first=Justin|date=9 April 2020|website=Vulture|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Lake Schatz of [[Consequence of Sound|''Consequence of Sound'']] described the song as an \"emotional number\" that \"[wrestles] with intimacy issues \u2014 especially during this time of social distancing\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/04/stream-charli-xcx-forever-new-song/|title=Charli XCX delivers new song \"Forever\" from quarantine: Stream|last=Schatz|first=Lake|date=9 April 2020|website=Consequence of Sound|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''\u2019s Jem Aswad felt that the song \"bears many of the hallmarks of the prolific artist\u2019s work over the past couple of year\", including Charli\u2019s two mixtapes. Calling the melody \"indelible\", Aswad mentions Cook\u2019s trademark \"echoing synthesizers\" and how Charli uses auto tune as an \"instrument in itself rather than as pitch correction\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-quarantine-album-listen-1234576093/|title=Charli XCX Drops New Song, \u2018Forever,\u2019 From Forthcoming Quarantine Album (Listen)|last=Aswad|first=Jem|last2=|first2=|date=|website=Variety|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Michael Love Michael of [[Paper (magazine)|''Paper'']], felt that the message of the song was about \" reminiscing about the good times with an ex\", and while Charli was \"singing about the future, the production and overall feel of 'Forever' couldn't sound more relevant\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/bops-only-joey-labeija-2645691331.html?rebelltitem=1#rebelltitem1?rebelltitem=1|title=Bops Only: 10 Songs You Need to Start Your Weekend Right|last=Michael|first=Michael Love|date=10 April 2020|website=PAPER|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> James from ''[[Stereogum]]'' described the song as \"perfectly goofy and giddy\", \"something that sounds ephemeral but feels like it will last forever\". James also felt that there was nothing \"nothing slapdash\" about the track, writing that the lyrics talked about a \"part of the compressed reality we\u2019re all experiencing: being trapped in close to someone that you care about\" as the single \"switches between abrasive and elated\", \"[choosing] to embrace happiness in the moment\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2079877/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week-330/franchises/the-5-best-songs-of-the-week|title=The 5 Best Songs Of The Week|last=James|first=|date=|website=Stereogum|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136824746|title=Credits / forever / Charli XCX \u2013 TIDAL|website=[[Tidal (service)]]|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Charli XCX]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting, backing vocals\n* [[A. G. Cook]] \u2013 production, songwriting, drum programming, programming, synthesizer, vocal production, xylophone\n* [[BJ Burton]] \u2013 production, songwriting, drum programming, programming, synthesizer, vocal production\n* Geoff Swan \u2013 mixing\n* Stuart Hawkes \u2013 mastering\n* Niko Battistini \u2013 assistant mix engineer\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Region\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Format\n! scope=\"col\" | Label\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Various\n| 9 April 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| <ref name= \"Apple Music\">{{cite web |title=forever - Single by Charli XCX on Apple Music|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/forever-single/1506988314|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate= 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Charli XCX}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Charli XCX songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Charli XCX]]\n\n{{2020s-single-stub}}\n", "name_user": "DontMindMeMkay", "label": "safe", "comment":